title: Due from Banks, National Banks for United States
notes:
Data Were Derived By Adding The Sum Of Three "Resources" -- Due From Reserve Agents; Due From National Banks; Due From State Banks. Monthly Coverage Varies From Year To Year. Except For 1874, Which Only Has Figures For October And December, All Other Years Have Scattered Five Month Coverage. Source: Computed By NBER Form Figures In Annual Report Of The Comptroller Of The Currency, 1916, Vol. Ii, Pp. 333-361.

This NBER data series m14032 appears on the NBER website in Chapter 14 at http://www.nber.org/databases/macrohistory/contents/chapter14.html.
